wikipedia_page.main: Liam Connor Norwell (born 27 December 1991) is an English cricketer who currently plays for Warwickshire. A right-handed batsman and right-hand medium pace bowler he made his first-class debut for Gloucestershire against Derbyshire in April 2011. Norwell signed a new two-year contract for Gloucestershire in 2013.

He appeared for Cheshire County Cricket Club in the 2018 Minor Counties Championship and for Worcestershire's Second XI before playing for South Australia's emerging cricketers side during the southern summer. In 2019 he played for Bradford and Bingley and was signed to a short-term contract by Warwickshire County Cricket Club as cover for the injured Liam Norwell. Wightman played for Warwickshire's Second XI but did not make an appearance in the first team. In 2021 he played for Derbyshire's Second XI before appearing in four matches for Kent's Second XI ahead of his first-class debut, having played club cricket for Tunbridge Wells Cricket Club in the Kent Cricket League during the season.
